research/history/logs/agent_action_0214.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此兼容性为直接兼容。当前 <0.5x 区域只有 topk@K64,EF1 这一个点，且它已经明显优于同成本附近的 factorized_topk；因此本轮不再继续纠缠 lowrank_factorized_residual 的 param_only policy 细节，而是直接回到最稳的低开销单库 family，在 EF=1 保持 encoder 成本约 0.25x 的前提下，把 K 提到 128，测试是否能在总成本仍约 0.37x、明显低于 0.5x 的条件下，把 FVU 从 0.2583 显著压低，补出第二个真正有价值的 <0.5x Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K128 在 <0.5x 内显著优于 K64 且吞吐下降可接受，则再回到同 family 只沿 K 轴补一个中间点。","如果 K128 的 FVU 改善有限但训练耗时或吞吐明显变差，则说明 EF=1 下继续加查表预算的边际收益不足，后续应转向新的低成本 family 而不是继续堆 K。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 的导出形式最干净：单静态字典上的有限加权和，直接兼容 LUTurbo，且是当前唯一已进入 <0.5x frontier 的 family。","r207/r208 已表明在低成本区 topk 明显强于 factorized_topk，但目前缺少同 family 在 <0.5x 区域内更高 K 的质量曲线点；本轮优先补这条最短链路前沿。","评估时必须同时比较 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，判断 K 增长带来的收益是否值得额外查表和训练时间。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮把主变量明确设为 architecture，并沿用历史已通过的 architecture action 形状：由 family_name 指定 family，不在 env_overrides 中重复写 ARCHITECTURE。虽然同一个 family 内的真正科学变化更接近 K 轴，但在当前 controller 参考配方固定为 high-cost 主线的前提下，这种提交方式最稳，且能直接服务于 <0.5x 区域补点目标。","summary":"切回直接兼容的 topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只把低开销单库路线的支持规模拉到 K=128，目标是在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的条件下，补出一个明显优于当前 0.31x 点的新 <0.5x Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0219.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"256"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；低秩 factorized scorer 只影响在线打分与选址，不改变 decoder 端仍是单库有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿链路，兼容性为直接兼容。r214-r218 已表明 topk@EF1 沿 K 轴继续加预算仍能改善 FVU，但最近两轮收益已明显变小且总耗时上升到 417s，说明单纯堆 topk 查表预算接近边际收益极限；本轮因此切到更低 encoder 成本的 factorized_topk，并把 K 提到 EF=1 下的满字典 256，测试是否能在总成本仍预计约 0.44x、继续位于 <0.5x 区域的前提下，用更便宜的 selector 换取更高可用 K，从而拿到接近或优于 topk@0.49x 的低开销 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 factorized_topk@EF1,K256 在 <0.5x 内接近或优于 topk@K248 的 FVU，说明低秩 scorer 路线在极低 EF 下仍值得保留，可继续围绕该 family 做低成本补点。","如果 factorized_topk@EF1,K256 仍明显落后于 topk，说明当前低开销区的关键不在 selector 降本而在表示本身，后续应转向其他兼容 family 而不是继续追 factorized scorer。"],"notes_to_memory":["factorized_topk 的 decoder 形式始终是单静态字典上的有限加权和，属于直接兼容 family；改变 scorer 结构不会破坏 LUTurbo 导出契约。","在 EF=1 下，factorized_topk 的 encoder 成本预计明显低于 topk，因此允许把 K 推到满字典而仍留在 <0.5x 区域；这是当前最有信息量的新 family 低开销 probe。","评估时必须同步检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认更便宜 scorer 是否带来真实系统收益，而不是只看终点 FVU。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮不再继续沿 topk 的 K 轴做更小边际收益的贴边补点，而是用一次新的直接兼容 architecture probe 回答更关键的问题：更便宜的 factorized selector 能否在 <0.5x 区域重新获得竞争力。风险是该 family 在历史低 K 点上偏弱，但当前 EF=1 且 K=256 的 regime 与以往不同，值得单轮验证。","summary":"切换到直接兼容的 factorized_topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，并把 K 提到 256，测试是否能在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的前提下，用更低 encoder 成本的 selector 获得接近或优于当前 topk 低开销前沿的 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0085.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` clearly weaker than the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the next and only justified matched architecture probe is `lowrank_residual_vq`. It preserves the same low-rank coarse-trunk intuition and static-library export contract while swapping staged residual selection for a harder discrete coarse assignment. If that discrete variant cannot materially challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` recipe, then hard residual-VQ is not worth continuing in the current LUTurbo-aligned regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 85 matched-probe rule: one probe only, one main variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remain fixed. I chose `lowrank_residual_vq` because it is a genuinely different but still LUTurbo-compatible decomposition pattern with stronger prior signal than simpler selector-only families. The main risk is that hard assignment raises brittleness and may underperform on curve smoothness even if early descent looks acceptable, which is why the full trajectory matters more than the final scalar alone.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual_vq` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpret this as a family-worthiness screen only: because hard residual-VQ can add discrete-selection brittleness, only a clear and stable quality advantage justifies future follow-up."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `lowrank_residual_vq` is clearly worse or less stable, keep focus on mainline loss/preprocess clarification rather than reopening more architecture variants immediately.","If it wins clearly, note it as a reserve candidate but still resume mainline recipe clarification next round before any further architecture churn."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 21 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=96` is a promising high-quality reduced-cost point: its curve kept descending smoothly through the late phase, and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` stayed very low. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis, lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping the `K=96` recipe fixed, to answer whether the new near-anchor deployment point is slightly over-regularized and can recover a bit more reconstruction quality without destabilizing training.","summary":"Run a single loss-axis test on the newly validated `K=96` topk point: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=96`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves the high-quality reduced-cost recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`other_param` via `AUXK_ALPHA`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed `K=96` curve shape. The main risk is that the gain may be small, but `K=96` is now the most promising reduced-cost point and its very low dead-feature pressure makes a clean over-regularization check more justified than continuing to remap K.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 21 established `K=96` as a strong high-quality reduced-cost point: late-phase FVU kept descending smoothly and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` remained near zero.","Because `K=96` is not capacity-stressed like the low-K regime, it is a better place than `K=8` or `K=16` to test whether the current auxiliary dead-feature pressure is slightly too strong.","This round returns from K mapping to recipe tuning, while still staying inside the same family and on a deployment-relevant point rather than retreating all the way to the K128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves `K=96`, keep the same K fixed and continue recipe refinement there before revisiting other K values.","If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` does not help, treat the current `K=96/signum/LR=1.6e-3` recipe as close to saturated and move to another single recipe axis.","If reducing `AUXK_ALPHA` hurts stability or quality, the current auxiliary pressure is likely already appropriate for this near-anchor reduced-cost point."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
