research/history/logs/agent_action_0030.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A clean rerun of the matched `gated` baseline at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum, lr=1.6e-3` will tell us whether Round 29 was a stable result with a healthy curve shape or a one-off; if it reproduces near 0.1499 with smooth descent, we should keep `gated` on the mainline and start the LR sweep next.","summary":"Round 29 already established the first matched `gated` control and it slightly leads the current frontier at `K=128`, so the highest-value next step is not to branch or change K, but to pay the clean-baseline tax the strategy asks for. This answers one question only: whether `gated` is genuinely competitive under the reference recipe, judged by both final FVU and the training-curve shape.","change_type":"no_change","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the required family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and follows the requested sequencing by filling the clean baseline before LR or optimizer changes. I am intentionally not proposing a new LR yet because reproducibility and curve shape are the blocking question after a first promising gated run.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 30 should be a clean control rerun for gated at the matched reference recipe: K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Use the rerun to inspect trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU; only start the LR sweep if the baseline reproduces cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean rerun reproduces with a smooth curve, try a conservative LR callback within gated, starting with 1.2e-3.","If the clean rerun is clearly worse or unstable versus Round 29, archive gated quickly and return to the topk mainline."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0143.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 architecture 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 为选出的稀疏系数，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，factorized_topk 不再使用 trunk、soft codebook 或两阶段 refinement，而是用低秩 scorer 做单库稀疏选择，仍保持静态库有限加权和的部署形式；在 EF=2 下其 encoder selection_cost 约 0.38x h×n，显著低于当前主线的约 1.25x，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，部署侧也只需单库 sparse lookup。本轮只回答一个 matched architecture probe 问题：在 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全不变时，这种更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续，还是它在当前低 EF regime 下会因表示能力不足而明显落后于现有 soft-codebook/two-stage 主线。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 factorized_topk 在大幅降低 selection_cost 的同时仅有有限 FVU 损失，则保留它作为低成本 LUTurbo 候选，但下一轮按策略回到主线 family。","若 factorized_topk 的 FVU 明显落后于 lowrank_residual 与 soft-codebook 系，则说明低秩单库 scorer 在当前 regime 下不值得继续，后续不再占用主线 probe 轮次。","若 factorized_topk 虽然更便宜但训练吞吐或总耗时没有优势，则将其视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭低 selection_cost 继续推进。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 Round 143 唯一允许的 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","r141 与 r142 已表明去掉 second stage、再去掉 soft codebook 都会出现阶梯式质量退化，因此本轮改测一条更低成本但机制不同的直接兼容候选，判断非全字典低秩 scorer 是否值得保留。","评估时必须同时比较 FVU、selection_cost、deploy cost、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免只按终点 SAE 指标判断架构价值。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守单变量原则与本轮 probe 约束：只改 architecture，未联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或其他 recipe。选择 factorized_topk，是因为它在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前所有兼容 frontier 点，且属于直接兼容的单库静态表示，能直接回答“更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续”这一独立架构问题。风险是该 family 在旧的高 EF regime 曾明显偏弱，但当前低 EF 成本约束已发生 regime shift，这正是本轮 probe 的信息价值所在。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成更低成本、直接兼容的 factorized_topk，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一次干净对照判断低秩单库选择机制在当前 LUTurbo 成本约束下是否仍值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because the policy layer validates `param_only` rounds against the current topk family best and only accepts one changed core axis, the deferred Adam callback cannot be isolated cleanly from the `signum@1.6e-3` reference. This round returns to the accepted mainline axis and changes only `LR`, setting `topk/signum/K128/EF12` to `1.7e-3` to resolve whether the useful region is a narrow band just above `1.6e-3` or whether the `1.8e-3` degradation already marks the onset of instability.","summary":"Stay on the topk mainline and do a pure signum learning-rate refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and move `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `1.7e-3` to answer one question about the local peak of the current stable recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This action is compatible with the stricter single-axis validator because only `lr` changes relative to the current topk reference recipe. It also stays within the active family and avoids another policy rejection while still extracting useful curve-shape information near the current best signum regime.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.7e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The policy validator for `param_only` currently accepts only one changed core axis relative to the family reference, so optimizer+LR callbacks must be deferred unless the reference optimizer changes.","Round 11 refines the active signum lane locally instead of reopening the rejected Adam callback path.","Judge this run by full curve shape around the late phase: if `1.7e-3` keeps descending smoothly it suggests `1.6e-3` was slightly conservative; if oscillation grows or late FVU degrades, the practical peak is at or below `1.6e-3`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `signum@1.7e-3` is better and still smooth, one final narrow LR check around `1.75e-3` may be justified before moving on.","If `signum@1.7e-3` is similar but less stable than `1.6e-3`, keep `1.6e-3` as the mainline anchor and stop LR refinement.","If `signum@1.7e-3` is clearly worse, treat `1.6e-3` as the stable optimum and only then reconsider how to legally explore optimizer changes under the validator."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
