research/history/logs/agent_action_0019.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 18 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=16` still maintained a negative late-phase FVU slope instead of fully stalling, even though dead-feature pressure rose sharply. This round changes only `K`, moving from `16` to `8`, to answer whether the current export-compatible topk recipe can still support one more major cost reduction before reconstruction quality and compensation burden become clearly impractical.","summary":"Continue the active topk low-K boundary search: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the practical LUTurbo cost-quality frontier extends below `K=16`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and follows directly from the observed `K=16` curve shape. The main risk is that `K=8` may push the recipe past the useful regime, but `K=16` still improved through the end rather than hard-plateauing, so the next clean question is whether the true boundary sits at `K=8` or between `8` and `16`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 18 (`K=16`) reached `FVU=0.3084372282028198`; the late-phase slope remained negative, so training was still improving rather than collapsing early.","At `K=16`, `dead_pct` and `auxk` rose sharply in the late phase, indicating meaningful capacity stress and likely growing reliance on online compensation if K is reduced further.","For LUTurbo, probing `K=8` is now the most informative single-variable action because it directly tests whether the current topk recipe still offers a viable lower-cost deployment point or whether `K=16` is already near the practical floor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` is still usable, run `K=4` to locate the hard lower bound of the current topk/signum regime.","If `K=8` degrades sharply or the late curve nearly flatlines, treat `K=16` as the current practical low-K boundary for this recipe.","If `K=8` is borderline, compare it against `K=16` as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
