research/history/logs/agent_action_0023.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 14 showed that lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` below the `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` reference did not improve FVU, which leaves the opposite loss-shaping question open: the current mainline may be slightly under-regularized rather than over-regularized. This round changes only `AUXK_ALPHA`, increasing it from `0.03125` to `0.0625` while keeping the exact K128 reference recipe fixed, to test whether stronger dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction or curve stability.","summary":"Run a single loss-axis check on the exact topk mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and raise `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.0625` to answer whether the current baseline benefits from stronger auxiliary pressure.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes no core axis relative to the declared mainline reference recipe, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and avoids repeating the invalid Round 22 pattern that mixed a non-core tweak with `K=96`. The main risk is that stronger auxiliary pressure could slightly hurt reconstruction, but after the weaker-aux test already failed on K128, this is the cleanest remaining single-variable loss-shaping question on the true reference backbone.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 22 was policy-rejected because the proposed `AUXK_ALPHA` change was coupled with `K=96` relative to the validator's mainline reference; non-core recipe tests need to stay on the exact reference backbone to remain isolatable.","Round 14 already tested weaker auxiliary pressure on the K128 mainline and did not improve FVU, so the remaining clean loss-axis question is whether stronger auxiliary pressure helps instead.","This round is judged by full curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if stronger `AUXK_ALPHA` smooths late training or improves reconstruction, the current baseline was slightly under-regularized; if not, the loss axis is likely saturated on the K128 recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` improves the K128 reference, continue refining the loss axis on the exact same backbone before returning to other recipe dimensions.","If stronger auxiliary pressure also fails to help, treat the mainline loss axis as saturated and move to a different single non-core recipe variable.","If stronger auxiliary pressure worsens late-stage FVU or stability, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` as the better-balanced mainline setting."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
