research/history/logs/agent_action_0221.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r β_r u_r + Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算 β_r 与 α_i，再执行 trunk 查表 + residual 查表 + 加权求和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。r220 的 blocker 不是质量，而是 TRUNK_RANK override 没有真正进入训练配置；当前执行链已具备 `TRUNK_RANK -> --trunk_rank -> sae.trunk_rank` 路径，因此本轮应严格锚定有效参考轮 r210，只改一个 env 参数 `TRUNK_RANK=32`，先验证 `research/history/logs/round*.config.json` 与 checkpoint `config.json` 都记录 `sae.trunk_rank=32`，再判断该 family 是否能以预估 total_cost≈0.36x 保持显著优于 <0.5x 区域 topk 前沿的 FVU，同时保住其更高吞吐/更短总时长。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果配置审计通过且 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 仍明显优于 `topk@0.38x` 的 FVU=0.1968，并且吞吐接近 r210 的 166.6k tokens/s，则下一轮继续相对本轮单变量下探 `TRUNK_RANK=16`，寻找更低成本拐点。","如果配置审计通过但 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 的 FVU 退化过大，则仍保留这轮作为有效成本点，下一轮在同 family 内回退到更温和的 `TRUNK_RANK=64` 做单变量 bracket，而不是立即切去新 family。","如果这轮再次出现 `TRUNK_RANK` 未进入 runtime/checkpoint config，则停止解读任何 FVU，直接转入接线修复验证轮。"],"notes_to_memory":["r220 无效的根因是参数接线而非架构质量；下一轮必须把“参数确实进入 runtime_config 与 checkpoint config”作为第一判据。","本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1,TRUNK_RANK=32` 的 combined_ratio 约为 0.36x，显著低于 r210 的 0.69x，也低于当前 `topk@K248,EF1` 的 0.49x。","若该点质量接近 r210 的 FVU=0.1256，同时维持其约 166.6k tokens/s、291s 级别的训练代价，则会成为 <0.5x 区域比 topk 更强的高价值 Pareto 点。"],"reference_round":210,"self_review":"这轮继续遵守单变量原则：相对有效 reference r210 只改 `TRUNK_RANK`，不重复把 `ARCHITECTURE/K/EF/LR` 写进 patch，也不使用已经被审计标记无效的 r220 作为锚点。选择复跑 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 而不是直接去 `16`，是因为当前最高优先级是先消除变量隔离失效这个 blocker，并拿到第一条真实有效的低 trunk-rank 证据；在审计通过之前，不应把结果当成架构结论。","summary":"复跑 r220 的科学问题，但按合法 `param_only` 形式严格锚定有效参考轮 r210，仅下发 `TRUNK_RANK=32`。本轮先做参数生效确认，再评估 lowrank_factorized_residual 是否能以约 0.36x total_cost 进入 <0.5x Pareto 主前沿。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0059.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the matched `topk` probe came back only slightly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, the next highest-value single architecture question is whether a simpler export-compatible scoring path can retain most of the quality while offering a cheaper route for online selection and coefficient computation. `factorized_topk` keeps the same static-dictionary finite weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk/gated`, but replaces direct latent scoring with a low-rank mixing stage before top-k selection, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `factorized_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a LUTurbo-oriented family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 59 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `factorized_topk` is a stronger LUTurbo-oriented probe than opening another heavier residual family because it preserves the same export contract while plausibly reducing support-scoring complexity; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe understates its ceiling, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 showed that matched `topk` under the strengthened `gated` recipe is only modestly worse (`0.146999` vs `0.142923`), so simpler export-compatible architectures remain worth probing when the `gated` mainline stalls.","`factorized_topk` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to a low-rank scoring stage before top-k support selection.","Round 59 should judge `factorized_topk` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `factorized_topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `factorized_topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its scoring path may align better with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `factorized_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
