research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline now stalled for ten rounds and `group_topk` already coming back slightly but clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `bucketed_topk`: it preserves the same fixed-`K` static weighted-sum decoder contract while changing only the selector architecture to a simple input-conditioned bucket specialization. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `bucketed_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `bucketed_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:23:    "family_name": "bucketed_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 63 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `bucketed_topk` is a cleaner probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample and export-compatible, and it is a cleaner runtime-aligned probe than heavier multi-stage or multi-branch families because it only asks whether light selector specialization helps enough to matter at all.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:30:        "value": "bucketed_topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:51:      "Round 63 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `bucketed_topk` after `group_topk` proved only roughly competitive and not mainline-worthy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:52:      "`bucketed_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo export because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architecture change is confined to encoder-side bucket specialization before top-k selection.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:56:      "If `bucketed_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:57:      "If `bucketed_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible selector-specialization direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:58:      "If `bucketed_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:69:    "architecture": "bucketed_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:77:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `bucketed_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0063.json:78:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 63 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `bucketed_topk` is a cleaner probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample and export-compatible, and it is a cleaner runtime-aligned probe than heavier multi-stage or multi-branch families because it only asks whether light selector specialization helps enough to matter at all.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0163.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 是单样本门控后选出的稀疏系数，因此最终表示是单静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.0x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，且仍低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。本轮严格保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 不变，只将 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 改为 gated，回答唯一问题：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，增加简单门控是否足以让单库路线更接近主线质量，还是它仍会明显落后于带 trunk、soft-codebook 和 staged refinement 的主线结构。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 gated 明显落后于当前主线，则说明简单门控单库路线在当前 regime 下不值得继续，下一轮回到主线。","若 gated 与当前主线差距小于预期且运行代价更优，则记录其为低成本直接兼容备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 gated 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的系统级收益需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["gated 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为直接兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159-r162 已覆盖 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual、lowrank_residual、factorized_topk、topk；本轮补充 gated 这一剩余可行直接兼容低成本路线。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把质量差异与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 gated 是因为它是当前尚未在这一严格 matched 配方下补齐的可行直接兼容单库对照，能回答简单门控是否足以弥补纯 topk 路线表达不足这一剩余问题。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 gated，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断这种简单门控的直接兼容单库架构是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
