research/history/logs/agent_action_0076.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 75 closed the simplest single-stage `topk` alternative: under the matched `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3` recipe it was clearly worse than the `two_stage_residual` mainline, so the next and only remaining high-value matched architecture probe this round should target a different deployment tradeoff rather than another plain top-k variant. `jumprelu` is the best single yes/no probe because it preserves LUTurbo's static-library finite weighted-sum form while potentially reducing online selection complexity through thresholded support shaping instead of a full staged residual path. This round asks one question only: under the exact current mainline recipe, is `jumprelu` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain worth later consideration, or should it be ruled out as clearly inferior?","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `jumprelu`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its thresholded single-stage support path may lower LUTurbo online selection cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 76 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the rest of the recipe fixed. `jumprelu` is a better use of the single probe than another standard top-k family because it tests a distinct support-selection mechanism that may be cheaper to deploy online while still satisfying the export contract. The main risk is that prior matched probing under an earlier regime already suggested weak reconstruction quality, but this is still the most informative remaining architecture-worthiness check under the current mainline anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 76 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `jumprelu` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because it represents a distinct thresholded selector that may reduce LUTurbo online selection cost while preserving static exportability.","Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test only: compare matched `jumprelu@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `jumprelu` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `jumprelu` revisit available because its selector path may be cheaper to deploy.","If matched `jumprelu` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","If matched `jumprelu` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `jumprelu` as a high-priority later follow-up family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0195.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i；其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库中的固定向量，alpha_i 是每个样本在线选择得到的稀疏系数，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为直接兼容。主假设：在保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全 matched 的前提下，最朴素的 topk 单库架构是否仍值得作为极低部署成本、低选择成本的 LUTurbo 备选；若其 FVU 相比 lowrank_residual / lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 明显恶化，则说明 low-rank trunk 与 coarse branch 不是锦上添花，而是当前可用性的必要结构。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 topk 明显劣于 lowrank_residual，则下一轮回到主线，只调一个成本轴如 TRUNK_RANK、NUM_CODES 或 STAGE1_RATIO。","若 topk 以更低部署成本和更快训练吞吐表现出可接受 FVU，可将其保留为最简直接兼容基线支线。","继续避免 routed 与 bucketed matched probe，因为它们在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 超过 1.5×h×n 预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 matched architecture probe；除 architecture 外保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。","topk 的导出路径是单一静态字典库上的有限稀疏加权和，属直接兼容。","r192-r194 已逐步验证去掉 stage2、去掉 soft codebook、再改成 factorized scorer 都会带来明显 FVU 损失；本轮进一步测试去掉 low-rank trunk 后，最简单单库家族是否还有保留价值。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这是一个严格单变量的 matched probe，问题单一明确：最简直接兼容单库架构在当前低 EF regime 下是否还有 LUTurbo 价值。它不追求取代主线，而是为‘低成本极简基线是否应继续占据搜索注意力’给出清晰结论。","summary":"执行一个 matched architecture probe：将主线切到 topk，其余 recipe 保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。该架构的最终重构是单一静态字典库上的有限稀疏加权和，属直接兼容；本轮只回答一个问题，即最简单的 LUTurbo 直接兼容单库方案是否仍值得继续保留。","touched_files":[]}
