research/history/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"在 topk/signum 基线已建立后，本轮只下调学习率，检验基线曲线末段的更新噪声是否来自步长偏大；若是，则较小 LR 应该在不改 family/optimizer/K 的前提下带来更平滑的收敛并改善 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 topk，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量是学习率：从 8e-4 下调到 6e-4，回答“当前 signum+topk 基线是否因 LR 略大而限制了收敛质量”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这是按主线顺序进行的单变量 LR 回调，归因清晰。风险是收益可能有限，但相比直接换优化器或改 K，这一轮更符合当前策略，也更容易结合训练曲线判断是过冲/震荡还是单纯欠训练。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"6e-4"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 2 保持 topk/signum/K128/EF12 不变，只做 LR 回调以提高归因清晰度。","本轮重点看训练曲线是否更平滑、后段是否仍持续下降，而不只比较最终单点 FVU。","如果 6e-4 明显更稳且更优，后续可继续在 signum 下做小范围 LR 精调；如果更差或收敛更慢，再考虑换 optimizer。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 6e-4 改善了后段收敛和最终 FVU，下一轮继续只调 LR 做更细化回调。","如果 6e-4 过小导致下降变慢或 FVU 变差，下一轮可回到 8e-4 附近并改为更高或中间 LR。","如果 signum 在两档 LR 下都已明显平台化，再按顺序只改 optimizer 做同 family 对比。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:20:    "summary": "Round 36 changed the picture: `gated@96` is not just viable, it improved the frontier over the existing `topk@96` control, so the family has earned one more K-mapping round. Keep the anchored recipe fixed and step only `K` from `96` to `64`. This directly answers whether the `gated` advantage generalizes to the next adjacent frontier point. Read the full curve, not just the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes below the `topk@64` control (`0.1992608`), `gated` is a real high-K mainline candidate; if it drops back behind `topk`, then the family likely helps only in the upper-K regime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:51:      "Round 36 established that gated generalizes beyond K=128 by beating the matched topk control at K=96.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:55:      "If `gated@64` also beats `topk@64`, continue one more downward K probe because gated is shaping up as the stronger mainline family across multiple frontier points.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:56:      "If `gated@64` falls back behind `topk@64`, treat gated as a high-K specialist and preserve it mainly for K>=96."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:76:    "description": "Round 36 changed the picture: `gated@96` is not just viable, it improved the frontier over the existing `topk@96` control, so the family has earned one more K-mapping round. Keep the anchored recipe fixed and step only `K` from `96` to `64`. This directly answers whether the `gated` advantage generalizes to the next adjacent frontier point. Read the full curve, not just the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes below the `topk@64` control (`0.1992608`), `gated` is a real high-K mainline candidate; if it drops back behind `topk`, then the family likely helps only in the upper-K regime.",
