research/history/logs/agent_action_0150.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"该 probe 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，这个 matched probe 只去掉第二阶段 residual refinement，保持 K=128、EF=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与其余主 recipe 不变，因此它只回答一个问题：当前两阶段结构本身是否真的值得为约 1.25x 而不是 0.75x 的 encoder 选择成本继续付费，还是单阶段 soft-codebook 父节点已经给出更好的 LUTurbo 总成本-质量权衡。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 matched 的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 在明显更低 selection_cost 下只小幅损失 FVU，说明两阶段结构优势不足以覆盖其额外选择成本，下一轮按规则回到主线后应更谨慎看待该 family 的继续投入。","若 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 明显更差，说明当前两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下仍有真实结构价值，probe 完成后下一轮回到主线继续做 recipe 或成本轴工作。","若两者终点接近但 probe 训练更快、tokens_per_sec 更高，则把它记为更强的低成本对照点，但不在本轮直接切主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格只改 architecture，其余 K、EF、optimizer、LR 全部与主线参考配方一致。","lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 为扩展兼容 family，不属于不兼容候选，可合法进入兼容 frontier 对照。","该 probe 同时提供更贴近 LUTurbo 真实目标的对照，因为它把 encoder 选择成本从约 1.25x 降到约 0.75x，而部署查表成本仍在同一量级。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，避免把吞吐差异误读为纯架构质量结论。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针规则：只改 architecture，保持主线的 K、EXPANSION_FACTOR、OPTIMIZER、LR 与主要 recipe 不变。相比改成更远的 factorized_topk 或 lowrank_residual，这个 probe 与当前主线只有一个结构差异点，归因最干净，也最能回答“两阶段 refinement 本身值不值得继续”的问题。","summary":"执行一次严格 matched architecture probe：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成其单阶段父节点 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断两阶段结构本身是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0179.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the JumpReLU selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and their coefficients. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then execute `trunk lookup + thresholded sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The probe asks one question only: in the low-EF feasible regime, does learned thresholding provide a better architecture tradeoff than the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline, or should this family be ruled out. Encoder selection cost should stay in the feasible band at `EF=2`, so this should produce a real signal instead of a policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` underperforms the mainline on FVU or shows materially worse `tokens_per_sec`/runtime without compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: decode remains a finite weighted sum over a static low-rank trunk plus a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes selector-side activation sparsity.","This matched probe stays inside the likely feasible encoder-cost regime and is more informative than another routed/bucketed-style over-budget probe.","When scoring the run, inspect `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; a tiny quality gain with slower training is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe avoids another likely budget rejection and tests a remaining compatible architecture that can still deliver a clean go/no-go answer for the low-EF frontier.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-cost signal on whether learned thresholding is worth continuing versus the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0065.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline stalled for twelve rounds and recent single-stage selector probes (`group_topk`, `bucketed_topk`, `codebook_topk`) all failing to beat it, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `two_stage_residual`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over static libraries, but distributes the fixed `K=128` budget across two sequential residual passes. This round answers one question only: under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe, is that staged residual decomposition intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0206.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM","value":"256"}],"expected_win":"lower_encoder_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式仍为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 是单个静态向量库中的基向量；低秩 factor scorer 只影响在线选择分数，不改变最终 decoder 的单库查表 + 加权求和形式，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性为直接兼容。本轮保持 K=64、EF=2、optimizer、LR 不变，只单变量下调 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 到 256，目标是在保留当前 <0.5x 主点的查表链路长度不变时，进一步压低 encoder selection cost 与训练时延，争取拿到比 0.44x 更低、且 FVU 明显好于 K=32 的新低开销点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=256 在 K=64 下保持接近 r204 的 FVU，则继续单变量下探到 192 或 128，寻找 encoder cost 的更优拐点。","如果 FVU 明显恶化，则说明当前 <0.5x 区域主要受 scorer 容量限制，下一步应转向 topk 或 lowrank_residual 的低成本对照，而不是继续压 factorized hidden。"],"notes_to_memory":["r205 表明继续降 K 到 32 会带来较大 FVU 退化，因此下一步更值得固定 K=64，改走 encoder 降本轴。","factorized_topk 的 decoder 始终是单静态字典，不会因 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 改变导出形式；该轴对 LUTurbo 兼容性安全。"],"primary_variable":"factorized_hidden_dim","self_review":"该方案严格只改一个主变量，并且比继续压 K 更符合当前目标：在 <0.5x 区域寻找更好的 cost-FVU 折中，同时可能改善训练吞吐。风险在于 256 可能仍偏激进，但相比直接切到 K=32，预期更有机会保住 FVU。","summary":"固定 factorized_topk 的 K=64/EF=2/signum/LR=3e-3，只将 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 设为 256，测试在不缩短查表预算的前提下，能否通过更轻 scorer 把 total_cost 从 0.44x 继续下压，并维持优于 K=32 的低开销 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0194.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i；其中 low-rank trunk 项 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库上的加权和，residual 分支 Σ_i alpha_i b_i 可导出为静态 residual 字典上的稀疏加权和。factorized scorer 只改变在线选择打分路径，不改变最终 decoder 形式，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。主假设：在保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全 matched 的前提下，lowrank_factorized_residual 是否能以更低 encoder selection cost（约 0.5x h×n）提供一个仍值得保留的低成本支线；若 FVU 明显劣于 lowrank_residual，则说明 factorized scorer 在当前低 EF regime 下损失过大，不值得继续作为主线兼容方向。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_factorized_residual 明显劣于 lowrank_residual，则下一轮回到主线，只调一个成本轴如 TRUNK_RANK、NUM_CODES 或 STAGE1_RATIO。","若它在显著更低 selection_cost 下维持可接受 FVU 且训练更快，可将 factorized scorer 保留为低成本 selector 方向。","继续避免 routed 与 bucketed matched probe，因为它们在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 超过 1.5×h×n 预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 matched architecture probe；除 architecture 外保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。","lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出路径仍是 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态字典库的有限加权和，属扩展兼容。","r193 已确认 plain lowrank_residual 在 0.62x selection cost 下 FVU=0.0730；本轮进一步隔离 factorized scorer 是否值得用额外误差换更低选择成本。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这是一个严格单变量的 matched probe，科学问题单一明确：验证 factorized scorer 这类低成本选择机制在兼容 residual family 中是否值得继续。虽然其现有 frontier 点较弱，但它能直接回答‘更便宜的 selector 是否还能保住可用 FVU’这一部署相关问题，信息价值高于重复已失败的 soft-codebook siblings。","summary":"执行一个 matched architecture probe：将主线切到 lowrank_factorized_residual，其余 recipe 保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。该架构的最终重构仍是 trunk 静态库与 residual 静态字典上的有限加权和，属扩展兼容；本轮只回答一个问题，即 factorized scorer 带来的更低 encoder 成本是否足以让该 family 继续作为 LUTurbo 低成本候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0091.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`whitened_lowrank_residual` failed catastrophically at the matched K128 anchor, so the next matched architecture probe should avoid more whitening-style conditioning and instead test a different single-stage low-rank selector family. The most informative remaining probe is `lowrank_factorized_residual`: it preserves the low-rank trunk and static-library weighted-sum export path, but replaces the plain residual scorer with a factorized scorer. This answers one clean question: can a more structured single-stage selector recover enough of the two-stage mainline's quality to be worth continuing, or is the second residual stage itself the essential ingredient. If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants are likely not worth further follow-up in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_factorized_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. I am explicitly avoiding `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` because with the current batch-size-1 regime it collapses to ordinary top-k behavior and would not be an informative matched probe. The main risk is that `lowrank_factorized_residual` may add selector complexity without helping quality or LUTurbo online cost, so this should be judged strictly as a yes/no family-worthiness test before returning to the mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 91 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Avoid `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` in this batch-size-1 regime because its adaptive budget path degenerates to ordinary top-k and is not a meaningful architecture probe.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a structured single-stage low-rank selector; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, treat the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants as low priority and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a structured single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0058.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stable but non-improving for five rounds, the highest-value single matched architecture probe is the simplest directly compatible alternative: `topk`. It preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while potentially lowering online selection and coefficient cost relative to `gated`, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to be worth revisiting as a family, or does `gated` remain clearly superior even before runtime considerations are counted?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays smooth and closes most of the gap to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is still worth later family-level consideration because its deployment path is simpler; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 58 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the rest of the settled mainline recipe fixed. `topk` is the best probe candidate because it remains directly export-compatible for LUTurbo and offers a simpler online path than `gated`; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe may understate topk's ceiling, but that is acceptable here because this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen, not a new topk tuning campaign.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 is a single matched architecture probe inserted after five consecutive non-improving `gated` rounds; it must be judged only as a family-worthiness test, and the next round should return to the `gated` mainline regardless of outcome.","`topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo deployment because the reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; compared with `gated`, it may also lower online selection and coefficient-computation cost if quality remains competitive.","Judge this probe by full curve shape and endpoint relative to the current `gated@128` anchor: if `topk` is clearly worse across the trajectory, archive it under the current matched recipe; if it is competitive, record that as evidence that the simpler architecture may still deserve a later dedicated revisit."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and treat this probe as closed.","If matched `topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but keep one later topk revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a small training-quality gap.","If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later topk follow-up under its own lane."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0166.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0166.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on lowrank_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is \u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9: LUTurbo can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static sparse residual lookup over fixed vector libraries. The probe asks whether removing the soft-codebook coarse branch and second-stage refinement is still worth keeping as a materially cheaper, faster compatible architecture in the low-EF regime.",
