research/history/round_summaries/round_0195.json:65:    "architecture": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0195.json:74:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u4e2a matched architecture probe\uff1a\u5c06\u4e3b\u7ebf\u5207\u5230 topk\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 recipe \u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u8be5\u67b6\u6784\u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u662f\u5355\u4e00\u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u7a00\u758f\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u5c5e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u5373\u6700\u7b80\u5355\u7684 LUTurbo \u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u5355\u5e93\u65b9\u6848\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u4fdd\u7559\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:7:  "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:19:    "hypothesis": "After the matched `topk` probe came back only slightly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, the next highest-value single architecture question is whether a simpler export-compatible scoring path can retain most of the quality while offering a cheaper route for online selection and coefficient computation. `factorized_topk` keeps the same static-dictionary finite weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk/gated`, but replaces direct latent scoring with a low-rank mixing stage before top-k selection, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `factorized_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a LUTurbo-oriented family?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:23:    "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 59 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `factorized_topk` is a stronger LUTurbo-oriented probe than opening another heavier residual family because it preserves the same export contract while plausibly reducing support-scoring complexity; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe understates its ceiling, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:30:        "value": "factorized_topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:79:      "Round 58 showed that matched `topk` under the strengthened `gated` recipe is only modestly worse (`0.146999` vs `0.142923`), so simpler export-compatible architectures remain worth probing when the `gated` mainline stalls.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:80:      "`factorized_topk` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to a low-rank scoring stage before top-k support selection.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:81:      "Round 59 should judge `factorized_topk` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:84:      "If matched `factorized_topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:85:      "If matched `factorized_topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its scoring path may align better with LUTurbo online-cost goals.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:86:      "If matched `factorized_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:97:    "architecture": "factorized_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0059.json:106:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 59 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `factorized_topk` is a stronger LUTurbo-oriented probe than opening another heavier residual family because it preserves the same export contract while plausibly reducing support-scoring complexity; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe understates its ceiling, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `two_stage_residual` mainline now stalled for five rounds, Round 75 is the single allowed matched architecture probe. The highest-value yes/no question is whether the simplest directly compatible alternative, `topk`, is still strong enough under the exact current mainline recipe to deserve any later revisit. `topk` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while likely reducing online selection, coefficient, and lookup complexity versus a staged residual decomposition, so this probe asks one question only: at matched `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to remain deployment-relevant, or should it be treated as clearly inferior to `two_stage_residual`?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:20:    "summary": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its simpler single-stage lookup path may lower LUTurbo online cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 75 rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and the main recipe fixed. `topk` is the most informative matched probe because it is directly compatible with LUTurbo's export contract and has a materially simpler online path than `two_stage_residual`, so even a moderate training-quality gap could still be acceptable. The main risk is that `topk` is already known to be weaker in prior regimes, but this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen under the new mainline anchor rather than a commitment to switch families.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:30:        "value": "topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:75:      "Round 75 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `topk` against the current `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe, because `topk` is the simplest directly compatible LUTurbo candidate and may reduce online selection and compensation cost despite weaker reconstruction.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:76:      "Judge this probe as a family-worthiness test, not a recipe-tuning round: compare the full curve of matched `topk@128` against the `two_stage_residual` reference at fixed `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, then return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:79:      "If matched `topk` is reasonably close with a healthy curve, return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round but keep one later `topk` revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a modest FVU gap.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:80:      "If matched `topk` is clearly worse than `two_stage_residual` across the curve, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0075.json:81:      "If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `two_stage_residual` reference, still return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round per policy, but record `topk` as the highest-priority later follow-up family."
