research/history/round_summaries/round_0193.json:65:    "architecture": "lowrank_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0193.json:74:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u4e2a matched architecture probe\uff1a\u5c06\u4e3b\u7ebf\u5207\u5230 lowrank_residual\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 recipe \u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u8be5\u67b6\u6784\u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u4e3a trunk \u9759\u6001\u5e93\u4e0e residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u5c5e\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u5373\u5728 LUTurbo \u6210\u672c\u7ea6\u675f\u4e0b\uff0c\u53bb\u6389 soft codebook coarse branch \u7684\u66f4\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u7236\u8282\u70b9\u662f\u5426\u8fd8\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u4fdd\u7559\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:79:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Round 21 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=96` is a promising high-quality reduced-cost point: its curve kept descending smoothly through the late phase, and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` stayed very low. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis, lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping the `K=96` recipe fixed, to answer whether the new near-anchor deployment point is slightly over-regularized and can recover a bit more reconstruction quality without destabilizing training.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:18:    "summary": "Run a single loss-axis test on the newly validated `K=96` topk point: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=96`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves the high-quality reduced-cost recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:21:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:23:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`other_param` via `AUXK_ALPHA`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed `K=96` curve shape. The main risk is that the gain may be small, but `K=96` is now the most promising reduced-cost point and its very low dead-feature pressure makes a clean over-regularization check more justified than continuing to remap K.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0022.json:28:        "value": "topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:20:    "summary": "Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:25:    "self_review": "This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:52:      "Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:55:      "If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:56:      "If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:76:    "description": "Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:77:    "self_review": "This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0152.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0152.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u8be5 matched probe \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u662f\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u56fa\u5b9a\u5411\u91cf\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0e\u4e3b\u7ebf\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9\u4e00\u81f4\uff0c\u4ec5\u628a architecture \u4ece lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6539\u4e3a topk\uff0c\u8fd9\u4e00\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF \u9884\u7b97\u5185\uff0c\u82e5\u53bb\u6389 low-rank trunk\u3001soft-codebook coarse branch \u4e0e two-stage refinement\uff0c\u53ea\u4fdd\u7559\u6700\u6734\u7d20\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u7a00\u758f\u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u91cd\u6784\u8d28\u91cf\u4f1a\u9000\u5316\u5230\u4ec0\u4e48\u7a0b\u5ea6\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u5224\u65ad\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u590d\u6742\u7ed3\u6784\u662f\u5426\u786e\u5b9e\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u6295\u5165\u7684\u67b6\u6784\u4ef7\u503c\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0152.json:20:    "summary": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u6b21\u4e25\u683c matched architecture probe\uff1a\u628a\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u6362\u6210\u6700\u7b80\u5355\u7684 topk\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5168\u90e8\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u7528\u4e00\u8f6e\u5e72\u51c0\u5bf9\u7167\u5224\u65ad\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u590d\u6742\u7ed3\u6784\u76f8\u5bf9\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u5355\u5e93\u65b9\u6848\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
