research/history/round_summaries/round_0144.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002low-rank trunk \u57fa\u5e93 U\u3001soft codebook \u9759\u6001\u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u53ef\u79bb\u7ebf\u5bfc\u51fa\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u6620\u5c04\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u65f6 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002\u7ecf\u8fc7 r141-r143 \u7684 matched architecture probes \u540e\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u5df2\u7ecf\u91cd\u65b0\u786e\u8ba4 two-stage soft-codebook \u4e3b\u7ebf\u5728\u8d28\u91cf\u4e0a\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e lowrank_soft_codebook_residual\u3001lowrank_residual \u4e0e factorized_topk\uff0c\u4f46\u8fd9\u4e9b probe \u7684\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u66f4\u77ed\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u8fd1\u671f\u8fd0\u884c\u4ee3\u4ef7\u7ed3\u8bba\u53ef\u80fd\u6df7\u6742\u4e86\u67b6\u6784\u5dee\u5f02\u800c\u975e\u4e3b\u7ebf recipe \u6f02\u79fb\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u56de\u5230\u4e3b\u7ebf\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual\u3001K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u505a\u4e00\u6b21 clean baseline \u590d\u9a8c\uff0c\u5f53\u524d feasible \u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684 FVU\u3001\u8bad\u7ec3\u66f2\u7ebf\u3001tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u4e0e final_total_tokens \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u7a33\u5b9a\u53ef\u590d\u73b0\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u4e3a\u540e\u7eed\u7ee7\u7eed\u505a\u4e3b\u7ebf recipe \u8c03\u6574\u63d0\u4f9b\u5e72\u51c0\u951a\u70b9\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0144.json:52:      "r141-r143 \u4e09\u4e2a matched architecture probes \u5df2\u628a\u66f4\u7b80\u5316\u5019\u9009\u7684\u8d28\u91cf\u4e0b\u754c\u770b\u6e05\uff1a\u5355\u9636\u6bb5 soft-codebook\u3001plain lowrank residual\u3001factorized_topk \u90fd\u672a\u8d85\u8fc7\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:7:  "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline stalled for eleven rounds and the lighter selector probes `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both coming back clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `codebook_topk`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite sum over static libraries, but it changes the architecture by adding a hard coarse codebook selection before the sparse residual. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `codebook_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `codebook_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:23:    "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 64 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `codebook_topk` is a better remaining probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample deployable, and it is more informative than heavier multi-branch gating because it tests a distinct static-library decomposition pattern that could plausibly trade some sparse support work for a coarse lookup plus residual correction.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:30:        "value": "codebook_topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:51:      "Round 64 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk` after `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both failed to beat the matched `gated` control.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:52:      "`codebook_topk` is extended-compatible with LUTurbo because the final reconstruction can be exported as a hard-selected static coarse codebook vector plus a finite weighted sum over a static residual decoder library.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:56:      "If `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:57:      "If `codebook_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible coarse-plus-residual deployment direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:58:      "If `codebook_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."
